          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch4ToDecimal",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a specific type of encoded numeric string, known as an overpunch, into a decimal number. Overpunch encoding is a method used in mainframe systems to represent signed numeric values within character strings, where the last character indicates the sign and the last digit of the number."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity level of this function is considered medium. While the logic for decoding overpunch characters is straightforward, it requires a good understanding of character encoding and the specific overpunch scheme used. The function involves conditional logic to interpret the last character of the input string correctly."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
